For each (c, d), compute ans based on the previous values. In Java, the loops are:

for (int c = A; c <= C; c++) {
    for (int d = B; d <= D; d++) {
        if (c == A && d == B) continue;
        ... compute ans ...
        dp[c][d] = ...;
    }
} In Fortran, the loops would be similar. But Fortran's do loops are inclusive. So:

do c = A, C
    do d = B, D
        if (c == A .and. d == B) cycle
        ...
